<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Hardened-runtime entitlements for the BUNDLED CHILD INTERPRETERS (node, python3)
  that Mycelium.app exec's as separate processes (src-tauri/src/main.rs spawns the
  Node server + :4711 supervisor; the Node server spawns python3 for the embed /
  clustering / transcribe / kokoro services).

  Under the hardened runtime, every exec'd binary is its OWN code-signing context,
  so these exceptions must be applied to node/python3 INDIVIDUALLY — they are NOT
  inherited from the parent .app. Tauri's bundler does not sign nested
  Resources/app/ binaries at all (tauri#8075), so scripts/sign-macos.sh applies
  this plist to them in the inside-out signing pass.

  Mirrors src-tauri/entitlements.plist (the app gets the same four):
    - allow-jit / allow-unsigned-executable-memory  → V8's JIT in the bundled Node
    - allow-dyld-environment-variables              → main.rs sets PATH/HF_HOME on children
    - disable-library-validation                    → python3 dlopen()s wheel .so /
      .dylib (faiss, onnxruntime, …) not signed by our Team ID

  See docs/DESIGN-macos-signed-distribution-2026-06-17.md §2-3.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables</key>
  <true/>
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
  <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
